    <h1>Fireworkz - Help</h1>

    <p>Install the <em>Fireworkz-Manuals</em> package to obtain the <em>Getting Started Guide</em> and <em>User Guide</em>.</p>

    <p>Install the <em>Fireworkz-Examples</em> package to obtain the tutorial files referred to in the <em>Getting Started Guide</em>.</p>


    <h2 id="OnlineResources">Online Resources</h2>

    <p>Many resources for Fireworkz are freely available <a href="http://croftnuisk.co.uk/coltsoft/fireworkz/">online</a>:</p>

    <ul>
        <li><a href="http://croftnuisk.co.uk/coltsoft/fireworkz/getting_started/">Getting Started Guide</a>;</li>
        <li><a href="http://croftnuisk.co.uk/coltsoft/fireworkz/user_guide/">User Guide</a>;</li>
        <li>
            <a href="http://croftnuisk.co.uk/coltsoft/fireworkz/addenda_and_errata/">Addenda and Errata</a>
            - updates since the documentation was printed, and errata therein;
        </li>
        <li><a href="http://croftnuisk.co.uk/coltsoft/fireworkz/hints_and_tips/">Hints and Tips</a>;</li>
        <li>
            <a href="http://croftnuisk.co.uk/coltsoft/fireworkz/downloads/">Downloads</a>
            - updated packages for RISC OS and example files, including those used in the <em>Getting Started Guide</em>;
            also Fireworkz for Windows and Fireworkz source code ZIP archive sets.
        </li>
    </ul>


    <h2 id="Support">Support</h2>

    <p>
        As Fireworkz is now completely free to use, support is a self-help affair.
        There is a Google Group <strong>colton-software-fireworkz</strong> where you may seek help from other users:<br />
        web site: <a href="http://groups.google.com/group/colton-software-fireworkz">http://groups.google.com/group/colton-software-fireworkz</a><br />
        e-mail: <a href="mailto:colton-software-fireworkz@googlegroups.com">colton-software-fireworkz@googlegroups.com</a><br />
        Please include files which demonstrate any problems (using a Spark or ZIP archive).
    </p>


